of instructions for the everyday conduct of prosperous Christians and the authors of these instruction manuals from 200 AD and links this examination with a study of attitudes towards the human body as revealed in the instructions. The volume shows how, far from denying the body, the standards relating to health display a legitimate concern for bodily well-being. At the same time, however, there is a fear of the body, which makes it necessary to keep it constantly under control. Key Features it makes a contribution to the intensive research at present being conducted into the "Second Sophistic" it combines historical, philological, and theological methods and insights it is also of relevance for the history of medicine.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/4.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aAlltagsleben. 4aFrühes Christentum. 4aMentalitätsgeschichte. 4aSpätantike. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aAntiquity.  aEarly Christianity.  aEveryday life.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2006z9783110277128oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2006z9783110276992oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311018920940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110891621zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110891621zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110891621/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGDb2006  aZDB-23-DGGb2006  aZDB-23-GCNc2000d2014  aZDB-23-GOA